body:
The code below does not product USERWARN.
```
module test
#(    parameter  WID = 1
)
(
    input wire [3:0] a,
    input wire [3:0] b,
    output wire  [1:0] c,
    output wire  [3:0]   d
);
initial if (WID==1) $warning("Bingo!");          
assign c = WID;
assign d = b;
endmodule : test
```

But, this code does
```
module test
#(    parameter  WID = 1
)
(
    input wire [3:0] a,
    input wire [3:0] b,
    output wire  [1:0] c,
    output wire  [3:0]   d
);
if (WID==1) $warning("Bingo!");          
assign c = WID;
assign d = b;
endmodule : test
```

Is that a feature or a bug?
